docs.abstract: New York’s not ready for Amazon’s HQ2, but here’s how the city can get there.
docs.snippet: New York’s not ready for Amazon’s HQ2, but here’s how the city can get there.
docs.lead_paragraph: After a nationwide campaign, Amazon selected Long Island City in New York as one of two locations for expanding its headquarters. The company’s decisions about whom it hires and how quickly, and where those workers choose to live, will affect how much the expansion changes the city. Jenny Schuetz from the Brookings Institution and Elizabeth Goldstein from the Municipal Art Society offer two views on how to prepare.

headline.main: Will Amazon Ruin or Revitalize New York City?

byline.original: By Jenny Schuetz and Elizabeth Goldstein

docs.abstract: After meeting with the governor and mayor, Amazon decided the men could put aside their differences, and it began to iron out a package worth over a billion dollars.
docs.snippet: After meeting with the governor and mayor, Amazon decided the men could put aside their differences, and it began to iron out a package worth over a billion dollars.
docs.lead_paragraph: On a late October day, Amazon executives flew to New York to answer a final question before they committed to opening a massive technology center in Queens: Could Gov. Andrew M. Cuomo and Mayor Bill de Blasio stop bickering long enough to see the project through?

headline.main: Before a Deal, Amazon Had to Know: Could Cuomo and De Blasio Get Along?
headline.print_headline: In New York and Virginia, Amazon Is Sold on a Deal

byline.original: By Karen Weise and J. David Goodman

docs.abstract: The company reported a net income of $2.9 billion in the third quarter, partly by being more efficient in its warehouses and data centers.
docs.snippet: The company reported a net income of $2.9 billion in the third quarter, partly by being more efficient in its warehouses and data centers.
docs.lead_paragraph: Amazon’s profits were hit or miss for its first couple of decades. But now, for the first time, they are starting to look consistent — with four consecutive quarters above $1 billion in profit.

headline.main: Amazon Squeezes Out More Profit as Sales Growth Slows
headline.print_headline: Sales Slow, But Amazon Clears Profit Of $1 Billion
